{{Infobox person | name = Binoy Mathew | image = Binoy Mathew on sets of wonder valley adfilm.jpg | caption = Binoy Mathew | birth_name = Binoy Mathew | birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1972|11|23}} | birth_place = [[Kadampanad]], Kerala, India | occupation = Ad Film director, screenplay writer, short story writer, cartoonist | spouse = Dr. Mary Binoy | children = Suzanne B. Mathew, Abu Binoy Mathew
}}
'''Binoy Mathew''' (born 23 November 1972) is an Indian ad film maker. He has directed advertising commercials for various brands in India.
==Early life and education== Binoy was born in the village of [[Kadampanad]], [[Kerala]] . He studied at Infant Jesus School, Thuvayoor, Boys High School, Kadampanad, Devasom Board College, Sasthamcotta (Bsc, Physics) and Rourkela Institute of management Studies (MBA). He gained experience in advertising and marketing while working with Sintex Industries Ltd., MK Electric Ltd., Schneider Electric Ltd., WaterMelon Studios Private Ltd. and Magiclite Productions.
==Career== Binoy started directing commercials with the IDCB Vanitha Easy Loan campaign and has worked on various brands <ref>{{cite web|title=Works Done|url= https://www.youtube.com/user/binoywm }}</ref> He also directed two animations shorts titled [[The Stealth]] and [[Walk and Talk (film)|Walk and Talk]]. The Stealth was selected for the prestigious Athens Anim Fest 2009.<ref>{{cite web|title=Athens Anim Fest 2009|url=http://www.animationcenter.gr/modules/news/article.php?storyid=371&sel_lang=englis|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130702035748/http://www.animationcenter.gr/modules/news/article.php?storyid=371&sel_lang=englis|dead-url=yes|archive-date=2 July 2013|accessdate=25 April 2013}}</ref> The premiere of the short film Walk and Talk took place at The Third International Documentary and Short Film Festival of Kerala<ref>{{cite web|title=Kerala Chalachithra Academy Archive|url=http://www.keralafilm.com/index.php/archive}}</ref> (idsffk),<ref>{{cite web|title=Idsffk 2010 bulletin|url=http://jinosampanayil.deviantart.com/art/IDSFFK-2010-Bulletin-167345199|accessdate=30 April 2013}}</ref> 2010, in the competition section of [[animation]] films.<ref>{{cite book|title=Festival book of Third International Documentary and Short Film Festival of Kerala|year=2010|publisher=Kerala State Chalachithra Academy|location=Thiruvananthapuram|page=55}}</ref>
