'''Chingiz Suleimanovich Labazanov''' ({{lang-ru|Чингиз Сулейманович Лабазанов}}; born 18 April 1991 in Bolshaya Martynovka, Russia)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wrestrus.ru/users/363 |title=Chingiz Labazanov |publisher=wrestrus.ru |accessdate=September 13, 2014}}</ref> is a [[Chechens|Chechen]]-born Russian Greco-Roman [[Wrestling|wrestler]]. He is winner Golden Grand Prix Ivan Poddubny in the Greco-Roman men's 74&nbsp;kg event and 75&nbsp;kg 2016, in final match he beat Olympic Champion [[Roman Vlasov]]. He is silver medalist in [[2014 FILA Wrestling World Cup - Men's Greco-Roman|Greco-Roman World Cup]] (two time) and gold medalist in [[2014 World Wrestling Championships|World Greco-Roman Wrestling Championships 2014]]. He became [[2015 Russian National Greco-Roman Wrestling Championships|Russian National Greco-Roman Wrestling Champion 2015]] in 75&nbsp;kg. He has older brother [[Ibragim Labazanov]] Olympic wreslter.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tv100.ru/news/v-peterburge-zavershilsya-chempionat-po-greko-rimskoj-borbe-106345/ |title=Two Chechens brothers are nationals champs |publisher=tv100.ru |accessdate=March 12, 2015}}</ref>

