'''Mahapratisara''' (Ch: 大随求菩薩; Jp: ''Daizuigu'') is a [[Bodhisattva]] belonging to the Mahayana and Vajrayana sects.<ref>''Indian Civilization and Culture'' by Suhas Chatterjee  p.307 [https://books.google.com/books?id=KItocaxbibUC&pg=PA307]</ref> She is sometimes presented as the consort of [[Vairocana]].<ref>''Kathmandu Valley painting: the Jucker collection'' by Hugo Kreijger, Ernst Jucker p.27 [https://books.google.com/books?id=5GZYdqAqjksC&pg=PA27]</ref> 

