== Fiction and Plays ==
Martin published ''The Big Domino in the Sky: And Other Atheistic Tales''<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Big Domino in the Sky: And Other Atheistic Tales|last=Martin|first=Michael|publisher=Prometheus Books|year=1996|isbn=978-1573921114|location=Amherst, NY|pages=|via=}}</ref> in 1996. This is a collection of short stories in various styles presenting philosophical arguments. {{ISBN|978-1573921114}}.

In 2011 Martin self-published a fiction novel,  ''Murder In Lecture Hall B'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.createspace.com/3685205|title="Murder In Lecture Hall B" by Mr Michael Martin|website=CreateSpace|access-date=2016-10-12}}</ref> about a murder in the classroom of a philosophy professor whose interests are Religions and Atheism. {{ISBN|9781466310063}}

Martin also wrote 8 short plays with moral or philosophical themes that are available on his website.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.profmichaelmartin.com/stage.htm|title=Michael Martin - Plays|website=www.profmichaelmartin.com|access-date=2016-10-12}}</ref>

