'''Nour El-Khoury''' (June 7, 1960 – 1998) was a [[Maronite]] Christian [[Lebanon|Lebanese]] woman. During the [[Lebanese Civil War|Lebanese war in the 1980s]], wounds appeared on the back of Nour’s hands and pieces of incense started to come out, accompanied by oil exuding, apparitions and messages from The Holy.

Her sociopolitical phenomenon got local and international media coverage, among which the local Maronite Christian media.

Six years after her death, on December 16, 2004, the smell of incense came out from her dress that was worn by her niece for a dress-up party, this was also covered by the Lebanese Christian Media.

